P.text:
 The guaranteed bonds to be issued by the guaranteed lender must
receive an underlying investment grade rating from a Rating Agency,
without regard to the guarantee;

 A term sheet summarizing the proposed terms and conditions of, and
the security pledged to assure the applicant's performance
under, the guarantee agreement;

 A statement by the applicant as to how it proposes to use the
proceeds of the guaranteed bonds, and the financial benefit it
anticipates deriving from participating in the program;

 Evidence of having been assigned an investment grade rating on the
debt obligations for which it is seeking the guarantee, without
regard to the guarantee;

 The applicant's demonstrated performance of financially sound
business practices as evidenced by reports of regulators, auditors
and credit rating agencies;

 The extent to which the applicant is subject to supervision,
examination, and safety and soundness regulation by an independent
federal agency;

 Counsel to the applicant must furnish an opinion satisfactory to
the Secretary as to the applicant being legally authorized to issue
the guaranteed bonds and enter into the bond documents;

 The applicant shall provide evidence of an investment grade rating
from a Rating Agency for the proposed guaranteed bond without regard
to the guarantee;

 Undertakings for the benefit of the holders of guaranteed bonds,
including: notices, registration, prohibited amendments, prohibited
transfers, indemnification, multiple bond issues;

 Pro forma projection of the guaranteed lender's balance sheet,
income statement, and statement of cash flows over the ensuing five
years;
